com.bluegosling.reflect

Class EnumType<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bluegosling.reflect.EnumType<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the enum values
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Comparator<T>

    public abstract class EnumType<T>
extends Object
implements Comparator<T>
    An enumeration of elements. In many ways, this is like a Class<Enum> except that it can be used for enumerations defined at runtime instead of at compile-time. In most other ways, this is like an immutable set of elements, but with the ability to query members by name or by ordinal position and to impose an ordering over members based on their ordinal position.
